06/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ministry for European integration says the government's action plan for EU accession was 80 per cent met as of the end of September, with 624 out of total 780 measures implemented. That marks a significant acceleration since the start of the year, when the rate was only 54 per cent.
In other news, Council of Europe Secretary General Walter Schwimmer is expected to arrive Tuesday for a two-day visit to Bucharest. Romania is marking its 10th anniversary of membership in the organisation. (ACT Media - 06/10/03)
